      <bioghist id="ref3">
         <head>Biographical/Historical note</head>
         <p>Includes original introduction by Richard H. Eastman, 1981, photocopy of biography of Leighton by Douglas A. Skoog, c. 1981, and photocopy of Leighton's manuscript, 1978, which concerns his viewing of the sunset from Point Arguello (Santa Barbara County), with a brief history of the exploration of California.</p>
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent id="ref4">
         <head>Scope and Contents note</head>
         <p>Leighton joined the Stanford University Dept. of Chemistry in 1928; he became a full professor in 1937 and served as executive head of the Department from 1939 until his retirement in 1954.</p>
      </scopecontent>
